==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Magneto-electricity
<hw>Mag`net*o-e`lec*tric"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Electricity evolved by the action of magnets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>That branch of science which
treats of the development of electricity by the action of magnets; --
the counterpart of <xex>electro-magnetism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Magnetograph</ent>⟦br⟧
